				<td colspan="2"><span>I would chose to group with others over soloing any time, but due to work, social life, etc it's not always possible to commit myself to the large chunks of time necessary for grouping. The ability to log on for an hour or so and actually make a little progression through solo play was just enough to hold my interest in the game. 
<br />

<br />
I found AoE kiting effective, but rather unrewarding as it was quite monotonous and used only a minimal number of bard skills. Charm kiting on the other hand was far more enjoyable as made me feel like I was really utilizing the skills of my class. If charm kiting becomes impossible through this invisibility issue the only other option we will have to solo is chant kiting. I have seldom tried this method, but I do remember it was even more mind-numbing than AoE kiting.
<br />

<br />
My bard is only a few months old so I am fairly new to the class. Its funny, but it seems that the very attributes that attracted me to bards in the first place have recently nerfed/changed or are about to taken away. 
<br />

<br />
Ironic actually as I camped the Sarnak Courier last week for my Goblin Gazughi ring - guess its going to useless soon hehe.
<br />

<br />
Riddem 59 Bard on Venril Sathir
<br />

<br />

<br />

